# Module Outputs Reference File Templates

The template will finally create the following outputs that can be pulled and used in subsequent terraform runs via data sources. The outputs will be written to the Terraform state file. When using and calling the module within a root project, the output values of the module are available to the project root by simply referencing the module outputs from the root project `outputs.tf` file.

<br><br>

## :file_folder: Module outputs.tf Reference File

```terraform
##############################################
# {{ var.Config.Repository.RepoName|default(ExModuleRepoURL, true) }} Available Module Outputs:
##############################################
{% for output in var.TFOutputs %}
output "{{ output.Name }}" {
    {{ output.Output }}
}
{% endfor %}
```

<br><br>

## :file_folder: Module Output Usage Reference File

```terraform
##############################################
# {{ var.Config.Repository.RepoName|default(ExModuleRepoURL, true) }} Module Output Usage:
##############################################
{% for output in var.TFOutputs %}
output "{{ output.Name }}" {
    value = module.{{ ExModuleName }}.{{ output.Name }}
}
{% endfor %}
```

<br><br>

> :spiral_notepad: &nbsp;[__Note:__](Note) <br> When referencing the module outputs be sure that the output value contains the identifier given to the module call. As an example, if the module was defined as `module "{{ ExModuleName }}" {}` then the output reference would be constructed as `module.{{ ExModuleName }}.{{ var.TFOutputs[0].Name|default("arn", true) }}`.

